<span id="xi.ii.xvi-p1"></span> <span class="c1"><span
id="xi.ii.xvi-p1.1"></span>Chapter XIV.</span>

<span id="xi.ii.xvi-p2"></span>“<span class="c22"><span
id="xi.ii.xvi-p2.1"></span>Then</span> why,” it is asked, “did the Deity
descend to such humiliation? Our faith is staggered to think that God,
that incomprehensible, inconceivable, and ineffable reality,
transcending all glory of greatness, wraps Himself up in the base
covering of humanity, so that His sublime operations as well are debased
by this admixture with the grovelling earth.”

